# CLAUDE.md
1. Don't assume. Don't hide confusion. Surface tradeoffs.
2. Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.
3. Touch only what you must. Clean up only your own mess.
4. Define success criteria. Loop until verified.
5. I run a 4-person startup. ~/work/private/ has financials and investor docs (read-only). ~/work/public/ is everything else.
6. Never edit anything in ~/work/private/. Drafts in ~/work/public/ are fine. If you're about to email an investor, stop and ask.
